(b)What is a function. Why do we use function?
ANS:->Function are modules of code that are used to perform a specific task.
Function can be used multiple times

They provide better modularity and high degree of code reusing.

(c)Explain the flow of execution when a function is called.
When a function is called
The program leaves the current section of code

Begins to execute the first line inside the function.

Code inside the function is executed from top to bottom.

When the program leaves th function, it goes back to where it started from.
